<aura:component controller="Einstein_PlaygroundController">

    <aura:attribute name="firstSection" type="String" />

    This Playground is an example showcase for how to use the Einstein Platform Services. It is provided as an
    <a href="https://github.com/muenzpraeger/salesforce-einstein-platform-apex/blob/master/LICENSE.md" target="_blank">open-source project AS IS</a>. Use it at your own fun and risk.

    <lightning:accordion activeSectionName="HowTo">
    
        <lightning:accordionSection name="HowTo" label="Playground How To">
            The basic workflow for using the Playground is:
            <ul>
                <li>- Create a dataset from a remote URL</li>
                <li>- Once labels are visible you can train the model.</li>
                <li>- When a model training has reached 100% you can run the prediction.</li>
            </ul>
            <br /> Check out the video to see the Playground in action.
            <br />
            <iframe width="420" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/poY8wR0pVks">
            </iframe>
        </lightning:accordionSection>
            <lightning:accordionSection name="Setup" label="Setup information">
                <div class="error">
                    <ul>
                            <li>- Set the value for
                                <strong>Einstein EMail</strong> in
                                <i>Setup => Custom Settings => Einstein Settings (via the "Manage" button)</i> for your org
                                to the email address that you've used to sign up for Einstein Platform.</li>
                            <li>- Store the certificate as certificate in the Certificate Management section of your org (DEPRECATED, OLD WAY => Store the Einstein Platform file as File in the org. The name must be
                                <i>einstein_platform_playground</i>).</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

        </lightning:accordionSection>
        <lightning:accordionSection name="Resources" label="Resources">
            <ul>
                <li>- Check out the documentation on
                    <a href="https://einstein.ai" target="_blank">Einstein.AI</a>.</li>
                <li>- Explore the Einstein_PredictionService Apex class and learn how to retrain models, get your API usage and
                    more.
                </li>
                <li>- Go to
                    <a href="https://trailhead.salesforce.com" target="_blank">Trailhead</a> and get hands-on by
                    <a target="_blank" href="https://trailhead.salesforce.com/en/projects/build-a-cat-rescue-app-that-recognizes-cat-breeds">building an app that recognizes cat breeds</a> with Einstein.</li>
            </ul>
        </lightning:accordionSection>
        <lightning:accordionSection name="Contribution" label="Contribution">You have ideas how to extend the Playground or the Apex wrappers? Great! Please read the
            <a href="https://github.com/muenzpraeger/salesforce-einstein-platform-apex/blob/master/CONTRIBUTION.md" target="_blank">contribution guidelines</a>.</lightning:accordionSection>
    </lightning:accordion>


</aura:component>